<h3>Setup</h3>

<ul>
    <li>2 common cards + 2 faction cards</li>
    
</ul>

<h3>Extra Rules</h3>
<ul>
    <li>No hand limit</li>
    <li>Gold can be used as food/wood/stone</li>
    <li>Empty faction decks do not get reshuffled</li>
    <li>"Draw from your discard pile" refers to your faction discard pile</li>
    <li>Open Production Locations
        <ul>
            <li>Send 1 worker (max) to an opponent's open production building</li>
            <li>Max 2 workers per open production per round</li>
            <li>You receive resource/card, they receive 1 worker</li>
            <li>Cannot activate your own open production location</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Production + Feature locations
        <ul>
            <li>Place in production row</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Sets
        <ul>
            <li>Group of 3</li>
            <li>Each card can be counted for more than one effect</li>
            <li>Cards include self when counting sets</li>
            <li>Production locations that check sets will include themself</li>
            <li>For features that count new sets, use facedown common cards to keep count</li>
            <li>Cannot exploit set-counting feature triggers with raze/rebuild</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Conquest
        <ul>
            <li>Can add defense tokens to faction locations
                <ul>
                    <li>+1 raze token</li>
                    <li>Max 1 of: defense token, printed token, samurai</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Conquer an opponent's <i>faction</i> location</li>
            <li>In any row, left-most (newest) costs 2 raze tokens, then 3, 4, 5, ...</li>
            <li>Remove any tokens/goods</li>
            <li>Add conquered location to <i>right-most</i> space on faction side</li>
            <li>Trigger production/feature effects, do <i>not</i> trigger building bonuses</li>
            <li>Defender receives 1 worker</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Fortresses
        <ul>
            <li>Fortress buildings are immune to all negative effects other than Siege</li>
            <li>Mark fortification level with a spare token, only clears with Siege action</li>
            <li>Siege: spend 2 raze tokens to clear an opponent's fortification</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>



<h3>End Game</h3>

<ul>
    <li>Common locations: 1vp</li>
    <li>Faction locations: 2vp</li>
    <li>Special location bonuses</li>
    <li>Tie:
        <ol>
            <li>Leftover workers & resources</li>
            <li>Most cards in hand</li>
        </ol>
    </li>
</ul>

